From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 07:18:10 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 25/25] Protocol v2: the external runtime supplies batch ids
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The store's driver registers a batch-id allocator
(unstable_registerBatchIdAllocator; second registration throws, error
606); getOrCreateBatchId (was getOrMintBatchToken) calls it at the one
batch-identity creation site — the empty slot-field arm of the
persistent per-lane Slot — and stores the returned id in slot.batchId
(was slot.token). Driverless usage falls back to a monotonic internal
counter, so the protocol works stock. The deferred flag becomes a
stored Slot field set at creation (the low-bit encoding dies); the
run-in-batch scheduling branch and the async-action park decision read
it; drivers learn deferredness via the allocator argument. Parked
settlement callbacks capture their batchId and no-op if the slot moved.
unstable_resetBatchRegistryForTest clears full slot tenancy (test-only,
never emits retirements, never resets the counter). Token/mint
vocabulary is gone from the protocol. Four protocol suites updated +
4 new pins (driverless fallback, double-registration throw, reset
tenancy scrub, parked self-invalidation across a reset): 41 passed.
Flow clean, lint clean, error codes extracted.
